Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria, Iberdrola: Spanish Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-06-23T06:44:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/banco-bilbao-vizcaya-argentaria-iberdrola-spanish-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  Spain ’s IBEX 35 declined 0.1 percent to 10,226.2 yesterday.  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  : Spain’s
second-largest lender agreed to issue new shares to bring
forward the conversion of 2 billion euros ($2.9 billion) of
mandatory convertible bonds issued in September 2009 to
anticipate new core capital criteria in Basel III banking rules.  The bank’s board also approved an interim dividend of 10
euro cents a share to be paid on July 8, an increase of 11
percent from a year earlier.  The shares fell 3 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 8 euros.  Iberdrola SA (IBE)  : The Spanish power company signed an
agreement for a five-year, 1.5 billion-euro loan and revolving
credit for the same amount that may be denominated in a
different currency. The shares added 4 cents, or 0.7 percent, to
6.13 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
